High Authority for the Protection of Personal Data ('HAPDP').&nbsp;
The HAPDP is composed of nine members chosen because of their legal and/or technical competence.&nbsp;
The HAPDP's role is to ensure that any processing of personal data is in accordance with the Law. In addition, the HAPDP's responsibilities include informing data controllers and data subjects of their rights and obligations, handling complaints, conducting audits, and sanctioning data controllers who are in breach of the Law.Last modified 10 Jan 2022
				
			